    "body": "Problem: Using `buf=0`/`win=0` context in `vim._with` should be equivalent to using explicit buffer/window identifier respectively.\r\n\r\nSolution: Explicitly adjust context in case of `buf=0` or `win=0`.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nFix #39136.\r\n\r\nWhile working on this, discovered several issues:\r\n\r\n- #39150\r\n- The `lua vim._with({ buf = vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf() }, vim.cmd.tabnew)` doesn't restore the buffer. This is not like with `win = vim.api.nvim_get_current_win()` and something that can only be fixed in C code (so outside of what I can help with).",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-18T16:04:28Z",
